Front End/UI Team Lead (React.JS, Redux, JavaScript, TypeScript)
Job ID: 97793
Who are we?
Every day, billions of transactions, calls and messages that hold the worldâs communications fabric together run on systems that Amdocs has helped create.
Because we work with some of the largest and most innovative companies on the planet, our work makes an impact. Over the past four decades, we have continually reinvented ourselves, and as we keep moving into exciting new areas such as media, gaming, IoT, 5G, cloud services and more, there are always opportunities for us to grow and develop. We will nurture your entrepreneurial instincts with open doors and promote your ability to seize the day. Our company comprises amazing people, a supportive atmosphere and a culture built on mutual support, respect and a âfeel good factorâ that can only happen in a workplace built by the kind of people Amdocs employs.
Make your career journey with us.
In one sentence
Responsible for leading and mentoring a small development team within a specific task or project, together with hands-on development.
All you need is...
Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or equivalent.
Total Experience - 5.5 to 8 years
Experience leading a Team - 1+ year
Extensive UI development experience with REACT, REDUX, JavaScript, TypeScript, ES6.
Understanding of HTML5/CSS3.
Experience of UI performance optimization techniques.
Proficient in using UML & in application of design patterns.
Exposure to REST paradigms and Domain/Resource modelling concepts and its integration with UI.
Exposure and understanding of usability, accessibility concepts.
Roles & Responsibilities
Provide leadership to software engineers by coaching and mentoring throughout end-to-end software development, maintenance, and lifecycle to achieve project goals to the required level of quality
Take ownership and accountability of the product and provides technical guidance, solution design for new requirements, problem resolution for critical / complex issues
Be responsible for Code quality and will ensure code is maintainable, scalable and supportable.
Represent and lead discussions related to product/application/modules/team and build relationships with internal customers/stakeholders
Enforces quality processes, measure them and takes corrective actions in case of variances and ensure all the project agreed deliverables are completed to the required level of quality.
Build relationships with internal customers/stakeholders
Estimating complex software application projects.
Partner with User Experience and Product teams to implement and augment the design.
Promote team engagement and motivation.
Why you will love this job:
â¢ You will be challenged with the leading and mentoring of a small development team.
â¢ You will be challenged with leading the technical aspects of the project.
â¢ You will have the opportunity to work in a growing organization, with ever growing opportunities for personal growth.
â¢ You will have the opportunity to work with the industryâs most advanced technologies.
